Calculation of the stationary velocity distribution function
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
To obtain velocity distribution we could calculate all moments 
\begin_inset Formula $\bigl\langle v^{2n}\bigr\rangle\Rightarrow$
\end_inset

 characteristic function whose Fourier transform is the distribution function
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Distribution function can be calculated much simpler with the Fokker-Planck
